• Explain the architecture

• Define system boundaries

• Describe software components

• Explain communication between services

• Guide implementation

• Ensure scalability

• Maintain consistency

---

# 2. Architecture Principles

The architecture follows several engineering principles.

## AI First

Artificial Intelligence is treated as a core service rather than an optional feature.

Every major feature is powered by AI.

---

## API First

Every feature must expose REST APIs.

The frontend communicates exclusively through APIs.

No direct database access is allowed.

---

## Modular Design

Each module owns a single responsibility.

Modules communicate using APIs or queues.

---

## Cloud Native

The platform is designed to run inside containers.

No component depends on local infrastructure.

---

## Event Driven

Long-running jobs never execute inside HTTP requests.

Heavy processing is delegated to background workers.

---

## Scalable

Every service should scale independently.

Frontend

Backend

Workers

Database

Cache

should all be independently scalable.

